# Consult `patterns/` when coding

**Mandatory rule:** after you fix a non-trivial bug or CI/deploy failure, add paired **`patterns/errors/`** + **`patterns/goldpath/`** entries — see [`document-fixes-in-patterns.mdc`](./document-fixes-in-patterns.mdc).

When writing or editing application code in this directory, or when using packages declared for this project:

0. Read [`patterns/README.md`](../../patterns/README.md) once per task if you have not recently — it defines **follow** (`goldpath/`) vs **avoid** (`errors/`) and naming conventions.
1. Check `patterns/errors/` for known anti-patterns to avoid duplicating past mistakes (skim filenames and optional `topics:` frontmatter when present).
2. Check `patterns/goldpath/` for preferred examples and doc-aligned snippets before inventing new patterns.

When the lesson is reusable, follow [`patterns-directory-for-agents.mdc`](./patterns-directory-for-agents.mdc) and the **mandatory** logging rule in [`document-fixes-in-patterns.mdc`](./document-fixes-in-patterns.mdc).
